    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A facet is a fundamental, homogeneous, and mutually exclusive category of information in a thesaurus (for example, the AAT has seven facets: Associated Concepts, Physical Attributes, Styles and Periods, Agents, Materials, Activities, Objects). </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051198/Harpring, Introduction to Controlled Vocabularies (2010)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000076166/ISO 25964-1:2011: Thesauri and Interoperability: Part 1 (2011)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Facetten zijn fundamentele, homogene en wederzijds exclusieve informatiecategorieën in een thesaurus. De AAT heeft bijvoorbeeld zeven facetten: Abstracte begrippen, Fysieke kenmerken, Stijlen en perioden, Actoren en organismen, Materialen, Activiteiten en Objecten.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
